00:31:58.590 --> 00:31:59.620
Don't be good.

00:31:59.620 --> 00:32:00.030
Be great.

00:32:00.030 --> 00:32:02.390
Anyone ever hear of a guy by
the name of Jim Collins?

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:09.500
He wrote a book called "Good to
Great." Jim Collins wrote

00:32:09.500 --> 00:32:13.030
this book, and he said, hmm, I
wonder if there's a way to

00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:16.590
determine how businesses just
kind of go along, and then

00:32:16.590 --> 00:32:18.820
they just shoot up at
a 45-degree angle.

00:32:18.820 --> 00:32:20.180
And they've been doing
this for years.

00:32:20.180 --> 00:32:21.830
And it's just within
the market trends

00:32:21.830 --> 00:32:22.990
and blah, blah, blah.

00:32:22.990 --> 00:32:26.120
What happened at that juncture
to cause them to go

00:32:26.120 --> 00:32:28.390
from good to great?

00:32:28.390 --> 00:32:30.335
And he thought, well, we could
design a research study, but

00:32:30.335 --> 00:32:33.180
that would take 50 years, 50
years to come up with the

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:35.610
analysis and see what
the results were.

00:32:35.610 --> 00:32:36.910
So instead he said,
you know what?

00:32:36.910 --> 00:32:38.580
Let's go to the stock
exchange.

00:32:38.580 --> 00:32:39.450
Let's look through that data.

00:32:39.450 --> 00:32:41.660
We've got gobs of data.

00:32:41.660 --> 00:32:45.450
And let's just see if
anyone did that.

00:32:45.450 --> 00:32:48.510
Sure enough, they had.

00:32:48.510 --> 00:32:51.360
Over all the years, they went
in and they looked at

00:32:51.360 --> 00:32:56.590
different categories of
companies in different years.

00:32:56.590 --> 00:32:59.850
And sure enough, boom.

00:32:59.850 --> 00:33:02.550
So they asked a very
simple question.

00:33:02.550 --> 00:33:04.280
What happened at
that juncture?

00:33:04.280 --> 00:33:06.100
What took these companies
from just doing

00:33:06.100 --> 00:33:09.360
whatever to being great?

00:33:09.360 --> 00:33:10.440
I'm going to summarize a bit.

00:33:10.440 --> 00:33:11.980
Normally I'd stretch this
out, but we don't

00:33:11.980 --> 00:33:14.760
have much more time.

00:33:14.760 --> 00:33:17.880
I want you guys to get it
though, "Good to Great."

00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:19.950
They came up with what they
call the three circles.

00:33:19.950 --> 00:33:21.510
I don't know why they call
them the three circles,

00:33:21.510 --> 00:33:24.400
because they got nothing to
do with circles really.

00:33:24.400 --> 00:33:26.620
They were three questions
put in a circle.

00:33:29.420 --> 00:33:33.700
First question, what are you
better at than anyone else on

00:33:33.700 --> 00:33:34.840
the planet?

00:33:34.840 --> 00:33:35.700
This is important stuff.

00:33:35.700 --> 00:33:37.860
You guys want to know how to
run a business and make

00:33:37.860 --> 00:33:38.820
success in your life?

00:33:38.820 --> 00:33:40.040
This is how you do it.

00:33:40.040 --> 00:33:42.340
I wish somebody had demanded
I read this book

00:33:42.340 --> 00:33:44.410
when I was like 12.

00:33:44.410 --> 00:33:48.810
Of course, it hadn't been
written then, but you know.

00:33:48.810 --> 00:33:53.000
What are you better at than
anyone else in the world?

00:33:53.000 --> 00:33:55.135
So for our little company,
we sat around and

00:33:55.135 --> 00:33:56.280
we discussed it.

00:33:56.280 --> 00:34:00.080
And we came up with a very
simple statement.

00:34:00.080 --> 00:34:04.930
We create the finest landscape
wilderness

00:34:04.930 --> 00:34:07.070
artwork on the planet.

00:34:07.070 --> 00:34:10.830
From click to ship, nobody
does it better.

00:34:10.830 --> 00:34:13.199
And I know, because we get
all of our materials

00:34:13.199 --> 00:34:14.469
from the same suppliers.

00:34:14.469 --> 00:34:15.889
And I know what other
people are using.

00:34:15.889 --> 00:34:19.889
And I know that I'm the only
one crazy enough to lug 120

00:34:19.889 --> 00:34:23.679
pounds of camera gear up over a
12,000 foot mountain pass to

00:34:23.679 --> 00:34:26.690
maybe get a shot.

00:34:26.690 --> 00:34:28.949
No one's doing it
at our level.

00:34:28.949 --> 00:34:32.120
Nobody on the planet is
even coming close.

00:34:32.120 --> 00:34:34.880
So I'll stand on my soap box,
and I'll say, bring it on.

00:34:34.880 --> 00:34:36.370
You want to put your piece
next to my piece,

00:34:36.370 --> 00:34:37.835
come on, I dare you.

00:34:37.835 --> 00:34:41.870
I've got my fourth-degree black
belt son backing me up.

00:34:41.870 --> 00:34:47.679
Second question, what drives
your economic engine?

00:34:47.679 --> 00:34:51.989
In other words, if you could
put a little box, which has

00:34:51.989 --> 00:34:55.370
got profit in it-- and profit
is created through x.

00:34:55.370 --> 00:34:57.940
x is the label on the box.

00:34:57.940 --> 00:35:01.190
What would that x be?

00:35:01.190 --> 00:35:03.290
So what drives your
economic engine?

00:35:03.290 --> 00:35:05.120
We thought about it.

00:35:05.120 --> 00:35:07.170
Didn't take that long
to figure out.

00:35:07.170 --> 00:35:10.140
For us it's profit
per piece sold.

00:35:10.140 --> 00:35:12.990
Every piece that we sell, the
most profit we can get out of

00:35:12.990 --> 00:35:14.460
it, better for us.

00:35:14.460 --> 00:35:16.600
There's lots of ways
you can do that.

00:35:16.600 --> 00:35:20.420
I could trim my expenses
in payroll.

00:35:20.420 --> 00:35:21.750
No one wants to hear that.

00:35:21.750 --> 00:35:23.570
I know, times are tough.

00:35:23.570 --> 00:35:24.270
I didn't do it.

00:35:24.270 --> 00:35:26.070
Haven't done it.

00:35:26.070 --> 00:35:28.940
You could beat up your suppliers
and get a better

00:35:28.940 --> 00:35:31.770
deal on your raw goods
materials, right?

00:35:31.770 --> 00:35:33.880
That will help increase
your profit.

00:35:33.880 --> 00:35:35.960
Maybe you don't discount.

00:35:35.960 --> 00:35:38.090
That would affect your profit.

00:35:38.090 --> 00:35:41.290
So for us the answer is, what
drives your economic engine?

00:35:41.290 --> 00:35:42.950
Profit per piece sold.

00:35:42.950 --> 00:35:44.790
For us, pretty simple.

00:35:44.790 --> 00:35:48.320
The last question that they
asked was they said, what are

00:35:48.320 --> 00:35:50.150
you passionate about?

00:35:50.150 --> 00:35:51.550
Because you have to have
passion in what you

00:35:51.550 --> 00:35:53.360
do, or forget it.

00:35:53.360 --> 00:35:54.130
Go home.

00:35:54.130 --> 00:35:56.220
Choose something else.

00:35:56.220 --> 00:35:59.220
For us it boiled down to our
mission statement, to enrich

00:35:59.220 --> 00:36:02.000
people's lives by bringing
Rodney's nature-based art into

00:36:02.000 --> 00:36:05.560
every home and office
in the world.

00:36:05.560 --> 00:36:05.870
Great.

